UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2584
1 A RESOLUTION endorsing the Ohio River Restoration Program Act to support
2 clean water, healthy fish and wildlife populations, economic development, and expanded
3 recreation opportunities in the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
4 WHEREAS, the Ohio River Restoration Program Act, House Resolution 5966 and
5 Senate Bill 3796, has been introduced in the United States Congress with bipartisan
6 support; and
7 WHEREAS, the Ohio River is one of the most significant rivers in the United
8 States, with a watershed that spans 15 states and provides drinking water, recreation, and
9 commercial opportunities for more than 30 million people; and
10 WHEREAS, the Ohio River forms Kentucky's northern border for approximately
11 664 miles, representing the longest Ohio River frontage of any state and touching
12 numerous Kentucky communities; and
13 WHEREAS, the Ohio River is a primary source of drinking water for hundreds of
14 thousands of Kentuckians, serving public water systems that supply communities
15 throughout northern, central, and western Kentucky; and
16 WHEREAS, the Ohio River and its tributaries drain a substantial portion of the
17 Commonwealth's land and are critical to Kentucky's agricultural productivity, industrial
18 operations, energy production, and municipal infrastructure; and
19 WHEREAS, Kentucky's river-based economy, which includes commercial
20 navigation, relies heavily on clean and reliable water supply, supports billions of dollars
21 in annual commerce, and creates thousands of jobs tied to manufacturing, shipping, and
22 related industries; and
23 WHEREAS, the Ohio River Basin supports a robust outdoor recreation economy in
24 Kentucky, including fishing, boating, paddling, and tourism activities that contribute to
25 local economies and improved quality of life; and
26 WHEREAS, the Ohio River is formed in part by tributaries that rise within or flow
27 though Kentucky. Pollution originating upstream or from within the Commonwealth
Page 1 of 2
