UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2584
1 directly affects drinking water treatment costs, public health, aquatic habitat, and
2 downstream communities; and
3 WHEREAS, despite its economic and ecological importance, the Ohio River
4 remains one of the most polluted rivers in the nation, and it continues to face challenges
5 related to nutrient pollution, toxic contamination, flooding, aging infrastructure, habitat
6 degradation, and invasive species; and
7 WHEREAS, House Resolution 5966 and Senate Bill 3796 would establish the Ohio
8 River Basin Restoration Program to improve water quality, increase flood resilience
9 through restoration of natural systems, protect and restore fish and wildlife habitat,
10 prevent and control invasive aquatic species, remediate toxic substances, enhance public
11 access and recreation, and improve outreach and education throughout the Ohio River
12 Basin; and
13 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth of Kentucky stands to benefit directly from a
14 coordinated Ohio River restoration effort through improved drinking water quality,
15 reduced water treatment and infrastructure costs, increased economic investment in river
16 communities, strengthened flood resilience, and expanded recreational and tourism
17 opportunities;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The Senate hereby expresses its support for House Resolution 5966
22 and Senate Bill 3796, the Ohio River Restoration Program Act, and recognizes its
23 importance to the Commonwealth by protecting our drinking water supplies,
24 strengthening the economy, and restoring the ecological health of the Ohio River Basin.
25 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
26 Resolution to the Kentucky congressional delegation.
